Pytorch 1.13.1
-----------------------------

Description
-----------
The modulefile AI/pytorch_23.02-1.13.1-py3 provides a Pytorch 1.13.1
development environment for Artificial Intelligence(AI)/Machine
Learning(ML)/Big Data(BD) on top of Python 3.

Module contents
---------------
Several popular libraries are included in this environment, such as:
    bokeh, matplotlib, mkl, numba, numpy, pandas, pillow, scikit-image,
scikit-learn, torchaudio, torchvision.

To check the full list of available packages in this environment, first
activate it and then run the command
    conda list

* beautifulsoup4 4.11.1
* blas 1.0
* bokeh 3.0.3
* cudatoolkit 10.1.243
* cudnn 8.0.4
* cython 0.29.32
* ipython 8.8.0
* matplotlib 3.6.2
* mkl 2021.4.0
* nccl 2.8.3.1
* notebook 6.5.2
* numba 0.55.1
* numpy 1.21.5
* pandas 1.5.2
* pillow 9.3.0
* python 3.10.9
* pytorch 1.13.1
* scikit-image 0.19.3
* scikit-learn 1.0.1
* scikit-learn-intelex 2021.20221004.171507
* scipy 1.10.0
* torch 1.13.1
* torchaudio 0.13.1
* torchvision 0.14.1

If you need to further customize this environment (e.g., install additional
packages, or upgrade a particular package),
you could first clone this environment as follows:
    conda create --prefix <path to a dir in which you can write> --clone $ENV
Then activate the newly spawned environment and proceed with your
customization.

To get further help with conda usage, you can try one of the following:
    conda -h
    conda <command> -h

